            <p><strong>Pre</strong><strong> </strong><strong>Primary</strong><strong>  </strong><strong>School</strong><strong> </strong><strong>Admission</strong><strong>  </strong><strong>Criteria</strong><br /> Pre Primary School Admission is granted on the basis of <br /> a) First come first serve basis<br /> b) Physically fit and mentally sound.<br /> c) And dialogue with the Parents of the child.</p>  <p><strong>Age eligibility</strong> (As on 31 December of the academic session for which admission is sought)                                                                               </p>  <p>(a) The child shall be of 3 & half + year for playgroup                                                                                                                                        (b) The child shall be of 4 & half + year for nursery<span>                                                                                                                                          </span>(c) The child shall be of  5 + year for KG<span>                                                                                                                                                         </span>(d) The child shall be of 6 + year for  Class one </p>  <p class="MsoNormal"><strong>Documents Required</strong><br /> A birth certificate as a proof of age from a civic body is required at the time of registration.<br /> Four copy passport sized photographs are to be submitted at the time of registration.<br /> <br /> <strong>Pre Primary School Admission Process</strong><br /> Pre Primary School ( Play to KG) Admission process in<strong> Orient School </strong>begins with counseling and completes on the receipt of admission fees and making the entry into the Record Register. <br /> <br /> In the record the groups are allocated based on age of the child and the age eligibility criteria and date of admission. <br /> <br /> <strong>For more information such as the  School Admission fee structure etc., kindly visit the visit our School. </strong></p>  <p class="MsoNormal">Our Admission Team is ready to work with you on processing your child's application to <strong>Orient School Mymensingh </strong>and get you started on their path to success. If questions should arise pertaining to any of the admission policies or procedures, please do not hesitate to call the admissions office or e-mail:</p>
        </div> <!-- /.box-content -->

